														<h3>What are your Hours of Operation?</h3>
														<p style="padding-left: 30px;">MON &#8211; FRI, 8AM &#8211; 4:00PM MST</p>
														<h3>Do you ship out of state?</h3>
														<ol>
															<li style="padding-left: 30px;">In 2014, the Farm Bill Sec 7606 allows us to legally produce our hemp which has been tested by the Department of Agriculture to have less than 0.3% THC. The Omnibus Bill defunds the Department of Justice from stopping transit of a hemp product which is protected by the Farm Bill Sec 7606. If you are having an issue with a receiving a package please contact our customer service representatives either by phone at 1-844-443-6764 or email at <a href="mailto:customerservice@purehempbotanicals.com">customerservice@purehempbotanicals.com</a>
															</li>
															<li style="padding-left: 30px;">Hemp oil, dietary hempseeds, and other hemp products are legal in all 50 states, but it is not legal to grow hemp in most states. Even though marijuana and hemp are two different plants, the federal government considers&nbsp;all&nbsp;cannabis plants a&nbsp;<a href="../4-reasons-why-hemp-should-not-be-considered-a-schedule-1-substance/index.html">Schedule 1 Substance</a>. According to&nbsp;<a href="http://www.votehemp.com/legislation.html">Vote Hemp</a>, only fifteen states— Colorado, California, Oregon, Montana, Nebraska, North Dakota, Utah, Kentucky, Indiana, South Carolina, Delaware, Vermont, Maine, West Virginia and Hawaii—allow industrial hemp farming for commercial purposes and/or research.&nbsp;This might change if the government passes the Industrial Hemp Farming Act of 2015. If you think that it should be legal to grow hemp in all 50 states, please let your senators and congressmen know by signing&nbsp;<a href="https://www.change.org/p/president-of-the-united-states-take-action-to-support-u-s-farmer-and-consumer-rights?just_created=true">our petition on Change.org</a>.
															</li>
														</ol>
														<h3>When will I know if my order shipped?</h3>
														<p style="padding-left: 30px;">Once your order ships from our facility you will receive an email with tracking information. We typically ship orders out within 24-48 hours during normal business days. Orders placed over the weekends or holidays will ship within 24-48 hours on the following business day.</p>
														<h3>Can you ship internationally?</h3>
														<p style="padding-left: 30px;">We currently are not shipping internationally.</p>
														<h3>How long will it take to get my package?</h3>
														<p style="padding-left: 30px;">Standard shipping through the US Postal Service via Priority Mail typically takes 2-4 business days depending on your location, although the post office does not guarantee delivery within this time frame.</p>
														<h3>Why have I not received my order?</h3>
														<p style="padding-left: 30px;">There may be many reasons why your package is delayed. Although we strive to provide quick shipping, we cannot control the package once it leaves our facility. If there is a problem with your package during transit, please contact our customer service team to investigate and resolve the issue either by phone at 1-844-443-6764 or email at customerservice@purehempbotanicals.com</p>
														<h3>What shipping methods do you use?</h3>
														<p style="padding-left: 30px;">We mainly utilize the US Postal Service to ship our packages.</p>
														<h3>How can I cancel my order?</h3>
														<p style="padding-left: 30px;">Please inform us as soon as possible. We tend to ship our orders out within 24-48 hours during business days. You can email us at customerservice@purehempbotanicals.com or call us at 1-844-443-6764.</p>
														<h3>What is your return/refund/exchange/replacement policy?</h3>
														<ol>
															<li style="padding-left: 30px;">Returns for a Refund: Must notify PHB within 14 business days of receiving product. Restocking fee of 20% of applicable product price may apply.</li>
															<li style="padding-left: 30px;">Exchanges: Must notify PHB within 14 business days of receiving the product. Restocking fee of 20% of applicable product price may apply.</li>
															<li style="padding-left: 30px;">Replacements for defective products: Typically at no cost to the customer except in cases of an exchanged replacement for product at a higher cost than the original.</li>
														</ol>
														<h3>Where can I purchase your products?</h3>
														<p style="padding-left: 30px;">Pure Hemp Botanicals does not have a retail store front; however we do have retailers who carry our products. You can view them on our website at: <a href="../retail-locations/index.html">https://purehempbotanicals.com/retail-locations</a></p>
														<h3>Do you offer wholesale pricing to retailers?</h3>
														<p style="padding-left: 30px;">Yes, we do offer wholesale pricing. Please send an email to <a href="mailto:sales@purehempbotanicals.com">sales@purehempbotanicals.com</a>, including a Contact Name, Company Name, Email address, Phone number, Best times to call and a brief description of your interests.</p>
