														<h3>Is CBD legal in my State?</h3>
														<p style="padding-left: 30px;">States hold their own laws regarding Hemp / CBD and the use of CBD products. We recommend that you check your state laws prior to purchasing.</p>
														<h3>Can I fail a drug test with the use of PHB Products?</h3>
														<ol>
															<li style="padding-left: 30px;">Our products are manufactured using hemp extract, defined by the Colorado Department of Agriculture as &#8220;a plant of the genus Cannabis and any part of the plant, whether growing or not, containing a delta-9 tetrahydrocannabinol(THC) concentration of no more than three-tenths of one percent (0.3%) on a dry weight basis.”</li>
															<li style="padding-left: 30px;">In simple terms, all our products may contain up to 0.3% THC. The THC amount in mg will vary depending on product suggested dosage therefore there is a possibility that consumption of the product could possibly trigger a positive test. Many drug screens tests for THC, which is the psychoactive compound of cannabis. If you have any concerns, please consult with a medical professional prior to purchasing our products.</li>
														</ol>
														<h3>How do I know how much to take or which strength to buy?</h3>
														<ol>
															<li style="padding-left: 30px;">There is not a standard dosage amount for CBD products. Everyone&#8217;s sensitivity to CBD varies, so we recommend that you start out low and adjust accordingly. Cannabidiol and other cannabinoids are known to be non-toxic, with no known fatal overdose levels ever reported.</li>
															<li style="padding-left: 30px;">Please refer to this chart to help give you an idea of what concentration you may need.&nbsp; If you&#8217;d like to speak with us regarding your unique situation, please contact our Customer Service Team at customerservice@purehempbotanicals.com / 1-844-443-6764. Please keep in mind that our customer service representatives are not medical professionals.</li>
														</ol>
														<p><img alt="" class="size-full wp-image-9254 aligncenter" height="1028" sizes="(max-width: 1600px) 100vw, 1600px" src="../wp-content/uploads/2017/03/Subscription-Table-Hompage1.png" srcset="https://purehempbotanicals.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/03/Subscription-Table-Hompage1-120x77.png 120w, https://purehempbotanicals.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/03/Subscription-Table-Hompage1-200x129.png 200w, https://purehempbotanicals.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/03/Subscription-Table-Hompage1-300x193.png 300w, https://purehempbotanicals.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/03/Subscription-Table-Hompage1-400x257.png 400w, https://purehempbotanicals.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/03/Subscription-Table-Hompage1-460x295.png 460w, https://purehempbotanicals.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/03/Subscription-Table-Hompage1-500x321.png 500w, https://purehempbotanicals.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/03/Subscription-Table-Hompage1-600x386.png 600w, https://purehempbotanicals.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/03/Subscription-Table-Hompage1-768x493.png 768w, https://purehempbotanicals.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/03/Subscription-Table-Hompage1-800x514.png 800w, https://purehempbotanicals.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/03/Subscription-Table-Hompage1-1024x658.png 1024w, https://purehempbotanicals.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/03/Subscription-Table-Hompage1-1200x771.png 1200w, https://purehempbotanicals.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/03/Subscription-Table-Hompage1.png 1600w" width="1600"></p>
														<h3>What are cannabinoids?</h3>
														<p style="padding-left: 30px;">Cannabinoids are the primary chemical compounds produced by the cannabis and hemp plant.&nbsp;Of the non-psychoactive cannabinoids,&nbsp;Cannabidiol (CBD) is the most widely known.</p>
														<h3>Can CBD products be used with my prescription medications?</h3>
														<p style="padding-left: 30px;">CBD or hemp is a natural plant based supplement that does not generally have adverse reactions with prescription drugs. However, you should always consult with your health care physician before making any medical decisions.</p>
														<h3>Do I need a doctor&#8217;s prescription or medical marijuana card to purchase your products?</h3>
														<p style="padding-left: 30px;">No, our products are classified as hemp so you are not required to have a prescription or medical marijuana card to purchase at this time.</p>
														<h3>What is CBD distillate and isolate?</h3>
														<p style="padding-left: 30px;">Distillate is a full spectrum, highly refined extracted oil that can be refined further. Full spectrum means that the product can contain both THC and CBD. CBD Isolate results from highly concentrated, purified CBD.</p>
														<p></p>
