														<p></p>
														<h3>What extraction methods do you use?</h3>
														<p style="padding-left: 30px;">We utilize Ethanol Extraction and other post-processing methods such as winterization and distillation to further refine and purify our oil.</p>
														<h3>How do I know how much CBD I am getting in my products?</h3>
														<p style="padding-left: 30px;">We clearly define all our products by the amount of CBD in the total product.</p>
														<h3>Are your products THC Free?</h3>
														<p style="padding-left: 30px;">Our products are manufactured using hemp extract, defined by the Colorado Department of Agriculture as &#8220;a plant of the genus Cannabis and any part of the plant, whether growing or not, containing a delta-9 tetrahydrocannabinol (THC) concentration of no more than three-tenths of one percent (0.3%) on a dry weight basis.&#8221; In simple terms, all our products may contain up to 0.3% THC. The THC amount in milligrams will vary depending on product suggested dosage.</p>
														<h3>How can I see the Lab Results for the product that I own?</h3>
														<p style="padding-left: 30px;">We provide a Certificates of Analysis (CoA), the lab results, for all our products and upload them for everyone to view. Each product will have its own identifying batch number which is used to pull up the lab results for the specified item. You can also view lab results by typing in key words such as &#8220;tincture&#8221; or &#8220;vape&#8221;. If you can’t locate a specific CoA, please reach out to Customer Service team. You can view them here: <a href="../lab-results/index.html">https://purehempbotanicals.com/lab-results/</a></p>
														<h3>Are any pesticides used on the plant matter used to manufacture the products?</h3>
														<p style="padding-left: 30px;">We do not use chemical pesticides on our Hemp plants and only use organic nutrients to grow them.</p>
														<h3>How can I see what ingredients are used in the products?</h3>
														<p style="padding-left: 30px;">To view the ingredients used in our products, please click on the desired product&#8217;s detail page and view the “Product Description” and “Additional Information” section to see the ingredients used in our products.</p>
														<h3>What is the difference between a softgel and a capsule?</h3>
														<p style="padding-left: 30px;">Soft gels are fully enclosed gel caps that are smoothly contoured and easy to swallow. The capsules are a vegetarian two-part capsule pressed together.</p>
														<h3>How should I store my products?</h3>
														<p style="padding-left: 30px;">To maximize the shelf life of your product please store in a cool, dry place. You can also store our products at room temperature or chilled in the refrigerator.</p>
