														<p></p>
														<h3>Can I refill my cartridge once the oil has been used up?</h3>
														<p style="padding-left: 30px;">Yes, our cartridges are refillable, however we cannot guarantee compatibility with the product you choose to refill it with. You can unscrew the mouth piece from the cartridge to refill it. Do not put the oil in the metal center piece of the glass covered cartridge or the cartridge will become unusable.</p>
														<h3>Can I use my own battery with the PHB vape cartridges?</h3>
														<p style="padding-left: 30px;">Our cartridges are compatible with 510 threaded batteries although we cannot guarantee effective compatibility.</p>
														<h3>Is distillate or isolate used in the formulation of the vape cartridges?</h3>
														<p style="padding-left: 30px;">We use a combination of both distillate and isolate for our vape cartridges.</p>
														<h3>What are Glycols used in the vape cartridges?</h3>
														<p style="padding-left: 30px;">Palm-based Propylene Glycol (PG) is used to formulate our vape cartridges.</p>
														<h3>How do I use a vape kit?</h3>
														<p style="padding-left: 30px;">The Vape Kit comes with one battery, one USB charger and one pre-filled cartridge with the flavor of your choice. Take the protective plastic cover off the bottom of the pre-filled cartridge. Screw the cartridge onto the battery. Press the button (located on the side of the battery base) 5 times, quickly and consecutively, to turn the battery on and off (this is indicated by blinking colorful lights). Hold down the button as you inhale and then let go of the button when you stop inhaling. To charge the battery, unscrew the cartridge from the battery. Ensure it is turned off by clicking the push button 5 times, quickly. Note: If you press the battery button once and it lights up around the push button, the battery is still on. Once the battery is turned off, screw the battery onto the USB charger and insert into a USB charging port. Once the light on the USB charger turns green the battery is full and ready for use.</p>
